title: Invasion Day rally evacuated after bomb threat; Beach visit hospitalises two men | 7NEWS Perth
description: After police found an improvised explosive device at an Invasion Day rally at Forrest Place, a 31-year-old male has been arrested and his house is currently being searched. Two men have been transported to hospital after allegedly getting caught in a rip at Mettams Pool. title: Extreme heatwave and fire danger grips southeast | 7NEWS
description: Severe heatwave warnings are in place across Victoria and South Australia with temperatures forecast to surge towards 50 degrees, prompting total fire bans and evacuation orders for thousands of residents in southwest Victoria as six bushfires burn out of control. Liberal Party leadership tensions escalate in Canberra as speculation mounts about a potential spill against Susan Ley, with conservatives divided between Andrew Hastie and Angus Taylor. Australia Day protests in Sydney saw rival rallies nearly clash with 1,500 police maintaining order, while a 31-year-old man was arrested in Perth after an explosive device containing ball bearings and screws was thrown into a crowd of protesters. title: Private jet crash in Maine kills seven | 7NEWS
description: A private jet crashed during takeoff at an airport in Maine, killing seven of the eight people on board, with only one crew member surviving with serious injuries. The incident occurred during a severe winter storm that has dumped up to 30 centimetres of snow across the United States from New Mexico to Maine, causing at least 12 deaths and cancelling 19,000 flights. Separately, US President Donald Trump has been urged to investigate the fatal shooting of 37-year-old nurse Alex Pretty by immigration agents in Minneapolis, the second fatal shooting by ICE agents sparking nationwide protests. title: At least 18 dead as Philippines ferry sinks
description: A ferry with more than 350 people on board has sunk in the southern Philippines, killing at least 18 people. The M/V Trisha Kerstin 3, an inter-island cargo and passenger ferry, was sailing to southern Jolo island in Sulu province from the port city of Zamboanga with 332 passengers and 27 crew members just after midnight on Sunday -- when it apparently encountered technical problems and sank.  Sea accidents are common in the Philippine archipelago because of frequent storms, badly maintained vessels, overcrowding and spotty enforcement of safety regulations, especially in remote provinces. #ferry #sink #Philippines #ship #rescue

title: Light plane crashes after takeoff killing two in Queensland | 7NEWS
description: A single-engine light plane crashed shortly after takeoff on the Gold Coast, killing both occupants including a 73-year-old pilot from Beenleigh and a passenger believed to be from Sydney.   The crash sparked scrub and cane field fires, with emergency services conducting a complex multi-agency response across difficult terrain including farmland, creek areas and muddy conditions.
